cleanliness reasons. that said, there's a dizzying number of sleeping options in most chinese towns, and despite language and legal barriers you should be able to find something in your budget and comfort range. finding a hotel when first arriving in a chinese city can be a daunting task: a mob of passengers is pushing to disembark from the train or bus, touts are tugging at your arm and screaming in your face to go with them, everything is in incomprehensible chinese and you are just looking for a place to put down your bag. it doesn't get any better 